<H1>William A. Rusher</H1>
</CENTER>

<p>
William A. Rusher served as publisher for <i>National Review</i> magazine from its founding in the 
mid-1950s to 1989.  He is a syndicated columnist, whose opinion essays appear in some 250 
newspapers nationwide, and a radio commentator for the Associated Press Radio Network.  He is
the author of several books, including <i>The Coming Battle for the Media</i>, <i>Special Counsel</i>, <i>The 
Making of the New Majority Party</i>, <i>How to Win Arguments</i>, and <i>The Rise of the Right</i>.  

