<TITLE>EDO Defense and Space Systems Home Page</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../gif/defense.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Welcome to the<BR>EDO Defense and Space Systems Home Page</CENTER>
</H2>

<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="combat/combhome.html">EDO Combat Systems</A>
| <A HREF="optics/optihome.html">EDO Electro-Optics (Barnes Engineering)</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="marine/marihome.html">EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems</A> | <A HREF="../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A>
] </CENTER><P><P><HR>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="combat/combhome.html">EDO Combat Systems</A> -- EDO
Combat Systems designs, develops and produces ASW sonar, digital
data link, and command and control systems for both domestic and
international customers. EDO has been a supplier of ASW sonar
systems for more than 40 years. It is emerging today as a supplier of low-cost, robust tactical data link systems for use
in shipboard, aircraft, mobile shore-based, and command center
environments. EDO Combat Systems provides complete logistics support
for its products, including installation and training, documentation,
spare and repair parts, and field service throughout the world.
</UL>

<P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="optics/optihome.html">EDO Electro-Optics (Barnes Engineering)</A> -- Servicing
the Satellite Industry for 40+ years, Barnes Engineering is a
producer of infrared earth horizon sensors. Barnes has
delivered in excess of 1,100 pieces of spaceflight hardware, including
earth sensors, payloads, and power supplies to diverse programs
such as the Defense Meteorological Satellite Program (DMSP), TIROS,
Landsat, Global Positioning Satellite (GPS), Tropical Rainfall
Measurement Mission (TRMM), COBE, RADARSAT, IRIDIUM&#153;, HS-601
and ORBCOMM&#153; Programs. In 1995 Barnes officially entered
the sun sensor market with its initial offering of a low-cost
analog sensor which, along with miniature static earth horizon
sensors, has been chosen to fly aboard the GLOBALSTAR constellation
of low earth orbit telecommunication satellites. Located in Shelton,
Connecticut, Barnes 65,000 square foot, state-of-the-art plant
is equipped to fabricate products to rigorous military and NASA
standards and includes a fully integrated infrared detector manufacturing
facility and in-house environmental test facility.  Barnes Engineering Company is a wholly-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation.
</UL>

<P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="marine/marihome.html">EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems</A>
-- EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems is focused on defense products and technologies for the U. S. and foreign nations with an emphasis on Mine Countermeasures and Suspension and Release Equipment for military aircraft.
</UL>
