<CENTER> [ <A HREF="products/optiprod.html">Products and Services</A>
| <A HREF="team.html">Our Team</A> | <A HREF="contact.html">Contact Us</A>
| <A HREF="../../invest/prlsmenu.html">EDO News</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../defehome.html">EDO Defense and Space Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ] </CENTER>
<P><P><HR>

<P>
<CENTER><STRONG><I>A World Leader<BR>in Design and Production of Infrared Earth Sensors<BR>for the Satellite Industry</I></STRONG></CENTER>
<P>
Servicing the Satellite Industry for 40+ years, EDO Electro-Optics (Barnes Engineering)
is a producer of infrared earth horizon sensors. Barnes
has delivered in excess of 1,100 pieces of spaceflight hardware,
including earth sensors, payloads, and power supplies to diverse
programs such as the Defense Meteorological Satellite Program
(DMSP), TIROS, Landsat, Global Positioning Satellite (GPS), Tropical
Rainfall Measurement Mission (TRMM), COBE, RADARSAT, IRIDIUM&#153;,
HS-601 and ORBCOMM&#153; Programs. In 1995 Barnes officially entered
the sun sensor market with its initial offering of a low-cost
analog sensor which, along with miniature static earth horizon
sensors, has been chosen to fly aboard the GLOBALSTAR constellation
of low earth orbit telecommunication satellites. Located in Shelton,
Connecticut, Barnes' 65,000 square foot, state-of-the-art plant
is equipped to fabricate products to rigorous military and NASA
standards and includes a fully integrated infrared detector manufacturing
facility and in-house environmental test facility. Barnes Engineering Company is a wholly-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation.<P><HR>

<P>
