<TITLE>EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems Home Page</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">
</HEAD><BODY><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/marine.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Welcome to the<BR>EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems Home Page</CENTER></H2><P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="products/mariprod.html">Products and Services</A>
| <A HREF="team.html">Our Team</A> | <A HREF="contact.html">Contact Us</A> | <A HREF="../../invest/prlsmenu.html">EDO News</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../defehome.html">EDO Defense and Space Systems Home
Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]</CENTER>
<P>
<P><HR>

<P>
EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems is  focused on defense products
and technologies for the United States as  well as foreign nations.
 These products and technologies represent the  principal mechanical
and electro-mechanical capabilities that reside  within EDO Corporation.
 
<P>
There are two major product lines within Marine and Aircraft Systems:
Mine Countermeasures and Suspension and Release Equipment for
military aircraft.   Both of these  areas require extensive engineering
expertise as well as fabrication and  systems integration capabilities.
 These product lines draw heavily on  the background and expertise
that EDO has developed in the aerospace  industry since its founding
in 1925. 
<P>
Another area that is developing into a separate product line is
Transportation.  EDO Marine and Aircraft Systems is able to  apply
certain electro-mechanical and electronic capabilities, originally
developed for military customers, to the transportation industry.

<P><HR>

