<HEAD>

<TITLE>EDO Ceramics Home Page</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/ceramics.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Welcome to the<BR>EDO Ceramics Home Page</CENTER></H2>

<CENTER> [ <A HREF="products/ceraprod.html">Products and Services</A> | <A HREF="team.html">Our Team</A> | <A HREF="contact.html">Contact Us</A>
| <A HREF="../../invest/prlsmenu.html">EDO News</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../induhome.html">EDO Industrial Products Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ] </CENTER>
<P><HR>

<P>
Since 1954, when EDO Corporation first established its piezoelectric
ceramics design and manufacturing capabilities, the company has
become the largest US based developer and producer of specialized
active piezoelectric ceramic components and devices. EDO produces
fourteen active piezoelectric material compositions and can produce
active ceramic material in virtually any shape and size. EDO continues
to aggressively research and develop new compositions to meet expanding market needs.
<P>
EDO Piezoelectric Products specializes in the development and
manufacture of piezoelectric actuators, sensors, transducers,
drive electronics and sub-systems for industrial, commercial,
medical and military applications.
<P>
EDO's Active Force Control Subsystem for Precision Machining is
currently under development. This system utilizes EDO's actuators,
sensors and electronics integrated into a grinding machine for
active force control while the machine is removing material. This
retrofitable subsystem will significantly enhance workpiece quality
and decrease throughput.
<P>EDO Acoustic Products and EDO Ceramics constitute EDO Western Corporation, a wholly-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation.

<P><HR>

