<TITLE>EDO Fiber Science Home Page</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/fiber.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Welcome to the<BR>EDO Fiber Science Home Page</CENTER>
</H2>

<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="products/fibeprod.html">Products and Services</A>
| <A HREF="team.html">Our Team</A> | <A HREF="contact.html">Contact Us</A>
| <A HREF="../../invest/prlsmenu.html">EDO News</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../induhome.html">EDO Industrial Products Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ] </CENTER>
<P><HR>

<P>
EDO Fiber Science is a developer and manufacturer (with full after-sale
support services) of high strength, light weight, filament wound
pressure tanks for gas and liquid containment, and large fiber-reinforced
wind turbine blades and stator cores for electrical power generation
systems. Tank applications include water and waste tanks for aircraft,
air tanks for over the road trucks and rail car pneumatic systems,
and fuel and pressurant tanks for aerospace applications. The
company provides turnkey design, development, testing, production
and aftersale support services.
<P>
EDO Fiber Science is organized into customer service teams comprising
of marketing, engineering, manufacturing and quality assurance
professionals who have the authority and responsibility to meet,
and if possible, exceed customer requirements and expectations.
<P>
EDO Fiber Science will soon be certified to the international
quality system ISO 9001 requirements and currently meets commercial,
military and other industry and customer quality standards. The
company emphasizes continuous manufacturing process improvement
using statistical process control and other methods to meet customer
product performance and reliability requirements
<P>
