<HEAD>

<TITLE>EDO Canada Ltd. Home Page</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/canada.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER>
<H3><CENTER>Welcome to the<BR>EDO Canada Ltd. Home Page</CENTER></H3>

<HR><P><Center><H3><I><B>NEWS FLASH: EDO Corporation has announced the decision to discontinue its participation in the alternative energy business.  Therefore, it is seeking interested investors for its energy-related businesses.  Anyone interested in acquiring EDO's interest in either or both of these businesses should contact <A HREF="mailto:investor.relations@edocorp.com ">Mr. William J. Frost at EDO Corporation, (718) 321-4000</A>.</B></I></H3></CENTER><P>
<HR>


<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="products/canaprod.html">Products and Services</A>
| <A HREF="team.html">Our Team</A> | <A HREF="contact.html">Contact Us</A>
| <A HREF="../../invest/prlsmenu.html">EDO News</A> ] </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../discont.html">Discontinued Operations Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ] </CENTER>
<P><HR>

<P>
EDO Canada Ltd. is the manufacturer of the all composite EDO LiteRider&#174;
Compressed Natural Gas Vehicle (NGV) Cylinder. The introduction
of the LiteRider&#174; cylinder in 1993 represented a significant
breakthrough for an industry that had been burdened by heavy,
low volume steel and aluminum cylinders required to store CNG
on-board vehicles. At 1/3 the weight of traditional steel tanks
and 1/2 the weight of aluminum tanks wrapped with fiberglass,
the EDO cylinder is not only the lightest in the world, but also
holds up to 30% more fuel that any other cylinder on the market.
Certified to the highest standards for NGV cylinders
(AGA/ANSI NGV-2; CGA B51 Part 2), the cylinder also meets the
criteria established by the US Department of Transportation's
FMVSS Standard #304.
<P>
EDO Canada Ltd. is an ISO 9001 registered manufacturing plant
and a joint venture between majority shareholder EDO Corporation,
the Government of Alberta, Canada, Toray Industries Inc (Japan)
and Sumitomo Corporation (Japan).
<P>
<A HREF="p-manufa.html"><B>Click Here</B></A> to see a photograph of the
manufacturing process of cylinders.
<P>
<A HREF="p-litede.html"><B>Click Here</B></A> to see a photograph of
a demonstration of lightweight properties.
<P>EDO Canada Ltd. is a majority-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation.

<P><HR>

