<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>EDO Corporation<BR>Declares Cash Dividend</CENTER></H2>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>COLLEGE POINT, NY - JANUARY 29, 1997 -- EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO)
 today announced that its Board of Directors has declared a quarterly cash dividend
 on its common stock of $0.025 per common share payable on March 31, 1997 to shareholders
 of record at the close of business on March 4, 1997.</DIV></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>Frank A. Fariello, Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer,
 stated: &quot;The Board of Directors is pleased to be in a position to reinstate
 a cash dividend of $.025, which has been suspended for the last two and a half years.&quot;</DIV></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>EDO Corporation is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced
 electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major
 prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment manufacturers. EDO also
 serves the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for 
military systems.</DIV></P>
