<P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>
  <B><I>Press Release</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif" ALIGN=BOTTOM BORDER=0 VSPACE=0 HSPACE=0>
</CENTER>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>
  [ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A>
  |<A HREF="../irmenu.html"> Investor Relations Home Page</A>
  |<A HREF="../../index.html"> EDO Corporation Home Page</A>
  ]<BR>
    <HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100% SIZE=2>
</CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
  <CENTER>
    EDO Corporation Takes Actions<BR>
    to Align All Shareholder Interests;
  </CENTER>
</H2>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
  <CENTER>
    Frank A. Fariello Elected<BR>
    Chairman of the Board of Directors;
  </CENTER>
</H2>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
  <CENTER>
    Ira Kaplan Appointed<BR>
    Executive Vice President<BR>
    and Chief Operating Officer
  </CENTER>
</H2>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  COLLEGE POINT, NY - JANUARY 29, 1997 -- The Board of Directors of EDO Corporation
  (NYSE:EDO) today announced that it has approved a reconfigured Director
  compensation plan designed to align the interests of EDO's Board of Directors
  with those of all shareholders. The new plan:
</DIV>
<P>
<OL>
  <P ALIGN=LEFT>
  <DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  </DIV>
  <LI>
    Increases the minimum number of common shares required to be held by a Director
    from 100 shares to 1,000 shares,
    <P ALIGN=LEFT>
    <DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
    </DIV>
  <LI>
    Requires a minimum of 50 percent of outside Director's retainer to be taken
    in common shares of EDO Corporation,
    <P>
  <LI>
    Discontinues the current retirement plan for outside directors, and
    <P>
  <LI>
    Establishes a new stock option plan for outside directors, subject to shareholder
    approval.
</OL>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  The Board also announced that it has elected Frank A. Fariello, 62, President
  and Chief Executive Officer, to the additional position of Chairman of the
  Board of Directors. Mr. Fariello succeeds Robert M. Hanisee, Managing Director
  of The Trust Company of the West, who continues as a Director of EDO. The
  Board also confirmed Mr. Fariello's appointment of Ira Kaplan, 61, as Executive
  Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of the Company.
</DIV>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  Mr. Fariello stated: "I take great pleasure in congratulating Ira Kaplan
  on his appointment as Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer.
  He has proven his ability to effectively manage and improve the diverse
  operations of our Defense and Space Business Units. His new responsibilities
  as COO will extend to all the Business Units of the Company. I am confident
  that his management skills and leadership qualities will result in the successful
  execution of the opportunities and challenges which face our Company today.
</DIV>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  "We would like to express our sincerest appreciation to Bob Hanisee for his
  leadership during these past difficult years. We are pleased that EDO will
  continue to benefit from Bob's sound judgment and experience by his service
  as a member of our Board."
</DIV>
<P ALIGN=LEFT>
<DIV ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
  EDO Corporation is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced
  electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products
  to major prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment
  manufacturers. EDO also serves the domestic and international defense markets
  as a prime contractor for military systems.
</DIV>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2><B><I>NOTE:</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Press releases and other
EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation world wide web site:
http://www.edocorp.com.</FONT>
<P>
<B>CONTACT:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  Van Negris<BR>
  Kehoe, White, Savage &amp; Co., Inc.<BR>
  (212) 888-1616
</BLOCKQUOTE>
