<P ALIGN=CENTER><CENTER><B><I>Press Release</I></B></CENTER></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif" ALIGN=BOTTOM BORDER=0 VSPACE=0 HSPACE=0></CENTER></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> |<A HREF="../irmenu.html"> 
Investor Relations Home Page</A> |<A HREF="../../index.html"> EDO Corporation Home
 Page</A> ]<BR><HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100% SIZE=2></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>Ira Kaplan Appointed<BR>Executive Vice President<BR>and Chief Operating Officer<BR>of
 EDO Corporation</CENTER></H2>
<P>COLLEGE POINT, NY - JANUARY 29, 1997 -- EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced
 that Ira Kaplan, 61, has been appointed to the posts of Executive Vice President
 and Chief Operating Officer. The announcement was made by Frank A. Fariello, Chairman,
 President and Chief Executive Officer.</P>
<P>Ira Kaplan has spent over 36 years at EDO Corporation, most recently serving as
 Vice President of the Defense and Space Systems Division. During his career at EDO,
 Mr. Kaplan has served as General Manager of the Government Systems Division and 
was an advisor to the U. S. Navy during the mine clearing of Haiphong Harbor after
 the end of the Vietnam conflict. Prior to joining EDO, he was a design engineer 
with Gibbs and Cox, a naval architecture and marine engineering firm. Mr. Kaplan 
holds a B. S. in Engineering from the College of the City of New York School of Engineering.
 He and his family reside in Plainview, New York.</P>
<P>Mr. Fariello stated: &quot;I take great pleasure in congratulating Ira Kaplan 
on his appointment as Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer. He has
 proven his ability to effectively manage and improve the diverse operations of our
 Defense and Space Business Units. His new responsibilities as COO will extend to
 all the Business Units of the Company. I am confident that his management skills
 and leadership qualities will result in the successful execution of the opportunities
 and challenges which face our Company today.&quot;</P>
<P>EDO Corporation is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical,
 electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense contractors
 and commercial original equipment manufacturers. EDO also serves the domestic and
 international defense markets as a prime contractor for military systems.</P>
<P><B><I>NOTE:</I></B> Press releases and other EDO information are available on 
the EDO Corporation world wide web site: http://www.edocorp.com.</P>
<P><B>CONTACT:</B></P>
<P><BLOCKQUOTE>Van Negris<BR>Kehoe, White, Savage &amp; Co., Inc.<BR>(212) 888-1616</BLOCKQUOTE>
