<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage &amp; Company, Inc.">
  <TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Appoints James Manchisi General Manager of EDO Electro-Optics</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<Center>
<I><B>Press Release</B></I>
<P ALIGN=Center>
<IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif">
<P>
[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> |
<A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> |
<A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]
  <HR>
<H2>
 EDO Corporation Appoints<BR>James Manchisi<BR>General Manager of<BR>EDO Electro-Optics </CENTER>
</H2>
<P>
COLLEGE POINT, NY - NOVEMBER 29, 1996 -- EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced that James Manchisi has been named General Manager of the EDO Electro-Optics business unit of EDO's Defense and Space Systems Division. <P>

Prior to joining EDO Corporation, Mr. Manchisi was the Director of the ChinaStar-1 Program at Lockheed Martin Astro Space in Princeton, New Jersey.  A recipient of many industry awards and honors, Mr. Manchisi is a graduate of General Electric's Advanced Course in Engineering and Edison Engineering Program.  Mr. Manchisi holds a Master of Science Degree in Computer Science from State University of New York (SUNY), Binghamton and a Bachelor of Engineering Degree in Electrical Engineering from Cooper Union.<P>

Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer, said:  "We are pleased to welcome Jim to EDO, where his years of management and marketing experience and keen understanding of the aerospace industry will prove to be an invaluable resource as EDO Electro-Optics moves to a new phase of growth."<P>

EDO Electro-Optics, a wholly-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation, is a leading supplier of spacecraft infrared Earth Horizon Sensors for spacecraft attitude control and commercial electro-optical instrumentation.<P>

EDO Corporation is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment manufacturers.  EDO also serves the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for military systems.<P>

<B><I>NOTE:</I></B> Press releases and other EDO information are available
on the EDO Corporation world wide web site: http://www.edocorp.com.
<P>
