<HEAD>
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage &amp; Company, Inc.">
  <TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Announces Receipt of Major Sonar Contract From An International Naval Customer; Contract to Materially Contribute to EDO's Order Backlog in Fourth Quarter </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P ALIGN=Center>
<I><B>Press Release</B></I>
<P ALIGN=Center>
<IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif">
<P ALIGN=Center>
[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> |
<A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> |
<A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]
  <HR>
<H2>
  <CENTER> EDO Corporation Announces<BR>Receipt of Major Sonar Contract<BR>From An International Naval Customer;<P>Contract to Materially Contribute to<BR>EDO's Order Backlog in Fourth Quarter </CENTER>
</H2>
<P>
COLLEGE POINT, NY - OCTOBER 21, 1996 - EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today that it has received, through its Defense and Space Systems Division (DSD), a major contract to provide sonar equipment to an international naval customer.  The contract, which is subject to receipt of a U.S. government export license, will materially contribute to EDO's order backlog in the fiscal 1996 fourth quarter.  Terms were not disclosed.<P>

EDO DSD's Combat Systems business unit, based in Chesapeake, Virginia, will manufacture and deliver a new sonar system, using state-of-the-art commercial off-the-shelf (COTS) components and software systems, to upgrade the previously installed EDO sonar systems of an entire class of the customer's naval fleet.  This new sonar will provide the international customer with a modern undersea warfare capability designed to counter a twenty-first century submarine threat.<P>

Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, stated:  "EDO has an installed base of over 80 operational sonar systems in service throughout the world.  This contract is a result of our long standing position as a leader in the international undersea warfare business.  Our  ability to capture this program in the very competitive international market is a result of our increased efficiency of operation.  In the coming year we will aggressively pursue additional orders for upgrades to other international EDO sonars."<P>

EDO is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical,
electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense
contractors and commercial original equipment manufacturers. EDO also serves
the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for
military systems.
<P>
<B><I>NOTE:</I></B> Press releases and other EDO information are available
on the EDO Corporation world wide web site: http://www.edocorp.com.
