<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Announces Receipt of $1.4 Million Command and Control Contract from Another NATO Nation </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Announces Receipt of<BR>$1.4 Million Command and Control Contract<BR>from Another NATO Nation </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY - OCTOBER 17, 1996 - EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today that it has received a contract valued at approximately $1.4 million from another NATO nation for Data Handling and Display Systems for the NATO Air Defense Ground Environment (NADGE) COTS-configured Ship-Shore-Ship Buffer (SSSB) Command, Control and Communications (C3) System Program.<P>

The contract is the second in a series of the NATO-wide NADGE command center upgrades for selected NATO countries.  The SSSB's Data Handling and Display Systems will provide C3 capabilities to NADGE's command centers with state-of-the-art software systems, commercial workstations, and communications systems.<P>

The SSSB's Data Handling and Display Systems will be manufactured by EDO Defense and Space Systems Division's Combat Systems business unit, based in Chesapeake, Virginia.  Deliveries are scheduled to be completed in early 1998.<P>

Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation stated: "This NATO contract, the second for our Combat Systems business unit, underscores our strong commitment to the growth of our international command-and-control team.  We look forward to adding these capabilities to the other NATO countries and we will continue to aggressively pursue additional NATO business opportunities and apply the full breadth of our advanced technology to building business in this new and exciting market."<P>

EDO is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment manufacturers. EDO also serves the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for military systems.<P>

<B><I>NOTE:</I></B>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation world wide web site: http://www.edocorp.com. <P>

