<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Awarded $1 Million Follow-On Earth Sensor Production Contract From Orbital Sciences Corporation </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Awarded<BR>$1 Million Follow-On<BR>Earth Sensor Production Contract<BR>From Orbital Sciences Corporation </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY - OCTOBER 16, 1996 -- EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced that its wholly owned subsidiary, EDO Electro-Optics, has been awarded a $1 million follow-on production contract from Orbital Sciences Corporation (OSC). EDO Electro-Optics will continue to supply miniature solid-state Earth Sensors for the ORBCOMM Global, Ltd. satellite constellation. ORBCOMM Global, Ltd., a partnership between Orbital Sciences Corporation and Teleglobe of Canada, provides two-way messaging and mobile data communications services.<P>

EDO will deliver infrared Earth Sensors to OSC through 1997 as the ORBCOMM satellites are built. EDO's Earth Sensors have already been successfully deployed on the first two ORBCOMM satellites, which began commercial service in February 1996. Upon completion, the ORBCOMM satellite constellation will consist of 28 satellites, with an additional 8 satellites to be produced as ground spares.<P>

Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer, stated, "This follow-on contract award builds on the excellent relationship we have established with Orbital Sciences. The development of EDO's low-cost, miniature Earth Sensor has resulted in our leading position in the growing market. EDO supplies Earth Sensors with proven, reliable technology to small and large satellite programs. The expansion of our contract with Orbital is further proof that we are succeeding with our strategy of acting as a specialty supplier of such niche products to prime satellite contractors."<P>

Orbital is a space and information systems company that designs, manufactures, operates and markets a broad range of affordable space and ground infrastructure systems, satellite access products and satellite services. These include launch vehicles, space sensors and electronics, satellite ground systems and software, satellite-based navigation and communications products, and satellite-delivered communications and Earth-imaging services.<P>

EDO Electro-Optics is a leading supplier of spacecraft infrared Earth Horizon Sensors for spacecraft attitude control and commercial electro-optical instrumentation.<P>

EDO is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment manufacturers. EDO also serves the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for military systems.<P>

<B><I>NOTE:</I></B>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation world wide web site: http://www.edocorp.com. Also, to learn more about Orbital Sciences Corporation, visit their web site at: http://www.orbital.com.<P>


<P>

