<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Announces Sale of Seaplane Float Operations </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Announces<BR>Sale of Seaplane Float Operations </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  OCTOBER 16, 1996  EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced the sale of its Seaplane Float operations to EDO Float Manufacturing LLC of Kirkland, Washington, an independent business entity established by Craig McCaw.  EDO's Seaplane Float operations had not constituted a material part of its business.<P>

Mr. Frank Fariello, President and CEO of EDO Corporation said:  "EDO Corporation is pleased to have served the seaplane float community for over 71 years.  We are confident that EDO Float Manufacturing will continue to provide the high quality products and services that have long been synonymous with EDO Floats."<P>

EDO is principally a supplier of proprietary advanced electro-optical, electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products to major prime defense contractors and commercial original equipment manufactures.  EDO also serves the domestic and international defense markets as a prime contractor for military systems.<P>

