<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO LiteRider Compressed Natural Gas Cylinder Selected by Honda Corporation for 1998 Natural Gas Civic Models </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO LiteRider Compressed Natural Gas Cylinder Selected by Honda Corporation for 1998 Natural Gas Civic Models </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  SEPTEMBER 16, 1996   EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today that Honda of America has selected EDO (Canada) Ltd. (ECL), a majority-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation, manufacturer of the LiteRider CNG cylinder, as the supplier of on-board fuel storage tanks for the 1998 Natural Gas Honda Civic. Tank selection for the Honda program was made public on September 15, 1996 by Honda of America at the AGA/NGVC Conference and Exhibition in Dallas, Texas.<P>

For the past two years,  EDO (Canada) has been working in close cooperation with Honda to develop a custom designed cylinder for the Civic. During this time, EDO (Canada), Ltd. has manufactured a number of prototype and pre-production cylinders which have been subjected to a series of standard and special tests to ensure suitability for use on the Civic under a variety of road and environmental conditions. Production levels have not yet been announced by Honda.<P>

Since their introduction in 1994, EDO LiteRider cylinders have offered OEMs and vehicle converters lightweight and high volume fuel storage capacity.  These cylinders have eliminated two of the most significant barriers to the widespread use of natural gas as a vehicle fuel: the heavy weight of traditional steel and aluminum cylinders and the limited range associated with natural gas.<P>

Mr. Frank Fariello, President and CEO of EDO Corporation said: "We are pleased and honored that Honda has chosen the LiteRider cylinder for the 1998 NGV Civic. The extensive design and  testing programs in  which we jointly participated ensure that Honda will use the most advanced design and construction in CNG fuel cylinders in the world. With weight and range being key issues for the lightweight Civic, the LiteRider cylinder was a logical choice as an integral part of Honda's plans for its NGV platforms. The Honda cylinders will be manufactured at EDO (Canada) Ltd., Calgary, Alberta."<P>

EDO Canada Ltd. is an ISO 9001 registered manufacturing facility and a joint venture of EDO Corporation, the government of the Province of Alberta, Toray Industries, Inc., Sumitomo Corporation, Japan, and Sumitomo Corporation of America.<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>

<B><I>NOTE:</I></B>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.<P>


<P>

<H4>CONTACT:</H4>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Van Negris<BR>
Kehoe, White, Savage & Co., Inc. <BR>
(212) 888-1616 <P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
