<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Appoints MAN Technologie AG as Exclusive Distributor for  LiteRider NGV Cylinders in Germany and Other European Markets </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Appoints<BR>MAN Technologie AG<BR>as Exclusive Distributor<BR>for  LiteRider NGV Cylinders<BR>in Germany and Other European Markets </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  August 14, 1996    EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced the appointment of  MAN Technologie AG of Germany as the exclusive distributor of EDO LiteRider compressed natural gas (CNG) vehicle cylinders to German and certain other European automotive markets and manufacturers.<P>

EDO's all-composite LiteRider cylinders, introduced in 1994, have offered the natural gas for vehicles (NGV) industry lightweight, high volume storage capacity by eliminating a primary obstacle to the widespread use of natural gas as a vehicle fuel: the extreme weight of the cylinders manufactured from aluminum and steel.  EDO's LiteRider cylinders are manufactured by the Company's EDO (Canada) Ltd. subsidiary.<P>

On the occasion of contract signature, Mr. Frank Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation said: "We are very pleased to welcome MAN Technologie AG as our exclusive European distributor of LiteRider cylinders.  Integral to EDO's strategy for addressing the international marketplace is a conscious plan to form strategic alliances with leading companies, such as MAN, who have an intimate market knowledge and the technical expertise to appropriately market the EDO LiteRider cylinder."<P>

Mr. Franz Denk, Vice President (Lightweight Systems) of MAN Technologie AG, added, in Munich, on the same occasion: "The LiteRider cylinder fits in well with the broad mix of equipment we supply to the European automotive, transit bus, and off-road industries. There are a number of significant markets in Europe that are making impressive advancements in the alternative fuels for vehicles industry.  EDO's LiteRider cylinder will enable us to address these markets with a leading edge technology."<P>

MAN Technologie AG is a member company of the MAN group, a company with DM 18 billion (US$11.2 billion) in annual turnover, and one of Europe's leading suppliers of capital goods.  The parent company services the transportation, aerospace, communications, plastics, energy, environmental, and construction industries and has a worldwide network of marketing and sales agencies and service centers.  MAN Technologie AG has annual sales of DM 306 million (US$201 million) and designs, manufactures, and represents space systems, lightweight systems, systems electronics and decentralized energy systems.<P>

EDO (Canada) Ltd. is a Calgary, Alberta-based ISO 9001 registered manufacturing plant and a joint venture of the Alberta Government, Toray Industries of Japan, Sumitomo Corporation of Japan, Sumitomo Corporation of America and majority shareholder EDO Corporation.<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>

<B><I>NOTE:</I></B>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.<P>


