<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Awarded U.S. Navy Contract to Lead NATO Influence Minesweep Study Program </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Awarded<BR>U.S. Navy Contract to Lead<BR>NATO Influence Minesweep Study Program </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  August 12, 1996    EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today that it has been awarded a contract by the U.S. Naval Surface Weapons Center, Coastal Systems Station, to lead, direct and integrate a multinational $2 Million study program of Next-generation Influence Minesweep Systems (NIMS). <P>

The NIMS program is a cooperative effort, being shared equally by the United States, Canada, Norway and France.  EDO's contract valued at $500,000 will be performed by its Defense and Space Systems Division, Marine and Aircraft Systems Business Unit, located in College Point, New York and will extend through early 1998.<P>

EDO has been involved in influence minesweeping for the U.S. Navy since the early 1970s with the MK-105 Airborne Minesweeping System which has performed successfully in major operations such as Haiphong Harbor, Suez Canal, Desert Shield and Desert Storm.<P>

Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, stated: "The selection of EDO to lead this multinational study demonstrates our prominence in the field and our commitment to remain at the forefront of this technology.  We anticipate that the international exposure afforded by this program will provide opportunities to expand our global Mine Countermeasures (MCM) relationships."<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>

