<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO ANGI Awarded $1,750,000 in Contracts for CNG/NGV Fueling Stations </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO ANGI Awarded $1,750,000 <BR>in Contracts for<BR>CNG/NGV Fueling Stations </CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  August 7, 1996    EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today reported that its EDO ANGI (EDO Automotive Natural Gas Inc.) business unit has been awarded a series of contracts, valued at $1,750,000, for several compressed natural gas (CNG) fueling stations for natural gas vehicles (NGV) to be installed in domestic and international locations.  EDO ANGI is the compressed natural gas fueling station packaging unit of EDO Energy, a wholly-owned subsidiary of EDO Corporation.<P>

Five complete NGV fueling stations, equipped with Ariel compressors, will be built for the Natural Gas Vehicles Company (NGVC), Cairo, Egypt, with deliveries scheduled to begin in October and continuing into early 1997.  NGVC, established in October, 1995 to develop, construct and operate the NGV infrastructure in Egypt, is jointly owned by Amoco Egypt Oil Company, the Egypt Gas Company and EMPI, which is a large in-country engineering and construction firm.<P>

Kern County Construction Inc., Bakersfield, California, has awarded EDO ANGI a contract for a complete compressed natural gas (CNG) fueling station, featuring an oil-free RIX 4VX compressor configuration. The station, scheduled for installation at the city of Arvin, California later this year, includes an EDO ANGI AMP III control system, gas dryer, storage, and single-hose fast fill dispenser.<P>

An EDO CNG fueling package, currently in final stages of installation and qualification, has been delivered to Great Falls Gas Company of Great Falls, Montana for use at a station that will supply fuel for the utility's own natural gas vehicles (NGVs) as well as those owned by private citizens and nearby fleets.  The 40 scfm RIX station package also includes an EDO ANGI AMP III control system, gas dryer, cascade storage, and dual-hose dispenser.<P>

Start-up and training services for all programs will be conducted by EDO ANGI's customer service department.<P>

Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer, stated:  "These contracts are a result of the concentrated and continued efforts EDO has put forth into establishing an important role in the NGV industry. For nearly fourteen years, EDO has provided a product and service base that has technically supported more than 250 CNG station sites across North America."<P>

EDO ANGI is a full service packager and manufacturer of compressed natural gas fueling stations and vehicle conversion equipment. Established in 1983 as Automotive Natural Gas Inc. the company is a pioneer of the alternative fuels industry and has installed more than 250 CNG refueling stations across the country, and distributed approximately 14,000 CNGV conversion kits to a broad spectrum of vehicle markets including passenger cars, trucks, school buses, forklifts, and marine vessels.<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>

<I>NOTE:</I>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.
<P>


