<head>
   <title>Press Release: EDO Corporation Awarded $5.2 Million Contract with $2.8 Million Option From McDonnell Douglas Aerospace for F-15E Bomb Release Units </title>
   <meta name="AUTHOR" content="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.01Gold (Win32)">
</head>
<body>
<!Copyright (c) 1996 by EDO Corporation - All Rights Reserved.>
<center><p><b><i>Press Release</i></b></p>

<p> <img src="edologo.gif" border=0 height=83 width=168></p></center>

<center><p>[ <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/invest/prlsmenu.html">List
of Press Releases</a> | <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/invest/irmenu.html">Investor
Relations Home Page</a> | <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/index.html">EDO
Corporation Home Page</a> ]</p></center>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h2 align=center>EDO Corporation Awarded
<br>$5.2 Million Contract with $2.8 Million Option
<br>From McDonnell Douglas Aerospace
<br>for F-15E Bomb Release Units </h2>

<p>COLLEGE POINT, NY - July 22, 1996 - EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced
today it has been awarded a $5.2 million ceiling price contract by McDonnell
Douglas Aerospace for BRU-46/A and BRU-47/A Bomb Release Units (BRUs) which
will be used on F-15E &quot;Eagle&quot; aircraft sold by McDonnell Douglas
to the U.S. Air Force. The contract contains option provisions for additional
quantities of BRUs at a not-to-exceed price of $2.8 million. Delivery of
the ordered units, which will be manufactured by EDO's Marine &amp; Aircraft
Systems Business Unit at its College Point, New York facilities, will start
in April 1997 and extend through May 1998 which will bring the total number
of units produced to over 4,500.</p>

<p> Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO
Corporation, stated: &quot;Stores release units continue to be an important
element of the defense segment of our business. This contract award represents
both a continuation and a strengthening of our relationship as a preferred
supplier to McDonnell Douglas.&quot;</p>

<p> Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical,
acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial
aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its
sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial
markets.</p>

<p> <i>NOTE:</i> Press releases and other EDO information are available
on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site: http://www.edocorp.com. </p>

