<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Awarded $2 Million Contract by U. S. Navy for Logistics Support of MK-105 Magnetic Minesweeping System</TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Awarded $2 Million Contract<BR>by U. S. Navy for Logistics Support<BR>of MK-105 Magnetic Minesweeping System
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY - July 19, 1996 - EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today it has been awarded a $2 million contract from the U.S. Naval Sea Systems Command for continuation of the logistics support of the MK 105 Mod 2 Airborne Magnetic Influence Minesweeping System. The contract will be performed entirely by EDO's Marine & Aircraft Systems Business Unit and will extend through the end of 1997.  The support includes the Scheduled Depot Level Maintenance (SDLM) of three (3) Systems, Evaluation and Repair of MK-105 Engines and the supply Depot Level Engineering and Technical Support Services.<P>

The MK-105 has been used in every U.S. Navy operational mine countermeasure operation including extensive use during Operation Desert Shield and Desert Storm.<P>

Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, stated:  "This latest award demonstrates EDO's position as one of world's leaders in the design, development and production of mine countermeasure systems, having contributed to the operational availability of the MK-105 by providing Depot Level support for the U.S. Navy for over 15 years."<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>

<I>NOTE:</I>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.
<P><P>

