<body>

<center><p><!Copyright (c) 1996 by EDO Corporation - All Rights Reserved.></p></center>

<center><p><b><i>Press Release</i></b></p></center>

<center><p><img src="edologo.gif" border=0 height=83 width=168></p></center>

<center><p>[ <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/invest/prlsmenu.html">List
of Press Releases</a> | <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/invest/irmenu.html">Investor
Relations Home Page</a> | <a href="http://www.edocorp.com/index.html">EDO
Corporation Home Page</a> ]</p></center>

<p>
<hr></p>

<center><h2>EDO Corporation Awarded 
<br>$2 Million Follow-On Contract 
<br>by Sparton Corporation;</center>

<center><p>EDO to Produce Ceramic Components 
<br>Used in U. S. Navy SSQ 62C Sonobuoy Program </h2></p></center>

<p>COLLEGE&nbsp;POINT, NY - July 18, 1996 - EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO)
announced today the receipt of a $2 million follow-on contract from Sparton
Corporation, Electronics Division, for active piezoelectric ceramic components
to be used in Foreign Military Sales (FMS) and in the U. S. Navy's AN/SSQ
62C sonobuoy program. The AN/SSQ 62C sonobuoy is an expendable, air deployed
device used for underwater acoustic surveillance. The original contract
award, valued at $3.3 million, was announced in April 1996.</p>

<p>The AN/SSQ 62C ceramic components will be manufactured by EDO Ceramics,
a business unit of EDO Corporation and the largest U.S. based developer
and producer of active piezoelectric ceramic components and devices. EDO
Ceramics also specializes in the development and manufacture of active
piezoelectric shapes, actuators, sensors, transducers and electronics for
industrial, commercial, medical and military applications.</p>

<p>Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO
Corporation, stated: &quot;EDO's commitment to supporting U. S. Navy programs
is reflected in our long standing relationship with quality prime contractors
such as Sparton. I consider EDO's on-going participation in this program
as another example of the strength of our core businesses' ability to supply
niche products to prime contractors because of our sophisticated technologies
and manufacturing capabilities.&quot;</p>

<p>Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical,
acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial
aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its
sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial
markets.</p>

<p><i>NOTE:</i> Press releases and other EDO information are available
on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site: http://www.edocorp.com. </p>

