<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Announces Contracts Totaling $3,380,000 for LiteRider All-Composite NGV Cylinders </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Announces<BR>Contracts Totaling $3,380,000 for<BR>LiteRider All-Composite NGV Cylinders 
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  June 25, 1996    EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced that its Canadian subsidiary, EDO (Canada) Ltd. ("EDO Canada"), has received $3,380,000 in contract awards for its LiteRider all-composite NGV (natural gas for vehicles) cylinders.<P>

Orion Bus Industries of Mississauga, Ontario has awarded EDO Canada a series of contracts for LiteRider cylinders destined for transit systems in San Bernadino, Oxnard, Monterey and Sacramento, California and in Toronto, Canada on Toronto Transit Commission passenger buses.<P>

Neoplan USA Corporation of Lamar, Colorado has awarded EDO Canada a follow-on contract for LiteRider cylinder assemblies destined for the Los Angeles County Metropolitan Transit Authority.  Each LiteRider cylinder package will provide a passenger bus with a CNG capacity of more than 16,000 scf and provide 400 miles per fill.<P>

Thomas Built Buses, Inc. (Chassis Division) of High Point, North Carolina has awarded EDO Canada a contract for three specially configured LiteRider cylinder packages for Thomas's upcoming fleet of natural gas powered buses.  Based on an earlier, successful prototype, these custom LiteRider configurations offer Thomas Built Buses the ability to simply, quickly and inexpensively convert each bus to natural gas power as its fleet rolls out.<P>

Frank Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, said:  "These contract awards are indicative of the growing acceptance of alternative fuels in commercial sectors, made possible by viable technologies such as EDO's LiteRider NGV cylinders.  We believe that our LiteRider cylinders, with their dramatically reduced weight and increased fuel volumes, are practical and cost-effective solutions for transit OEMs and transit authorities whose priorities focus on longer ranges, minimized maintenance costs and increased payloads." <P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, EDO Corporation continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.
<P><P>

