<HEAD>

<TITLE>Press Release:  EDO Corporation Joins Clean Air Team; Provides NGV Taxicab for Olympic Ride and Drive </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Joins Clean Air Team;<P>Provides NGV Taxicab for Olympic Ride and Drive 
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY -- June 4, 1996 -- EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) announced today that it has become a member of the "Clean Air Team", a group of NGV (natural gas for vehicles) industry members organized by the American Gas Association (AGA), an official Olympic sponsor, to support cleaner air for the 1996 Olympic Games which run from July 19th through August 4th, 1996 in Atlanta, Georgia.<P>

EDO, a recognized leader in the supply of equipment and services to the NGV (natural gas for vehicles) industry, is providing a Chevrolet Caprice taxicab, specially modified by EDO to run on CNG (compressed natural gas),  which will be on display in the AGA Showcase Display and also assist in the transportation of officials and visiting dignitaries throughout the Games.<P>

Frank Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, said:  "At EDO, we pride ourselves on our commitment to supporting a clean, safe, and economic alternative to traditional fuels.  We are honored and excited to be a member of the American Gas Association's Clean Air Team at the 1996 Summer Olympic Games.  We feel it is an ideal opportunity to send a message to the worldwide Olympic viewing audience that natural gas is available, convenient, and already successful across a broad spectrum of applications."<P>

EDO Corporation's support of the project reflects its strong involvement in the NGV industry.  Through its three energy-related business units, EDO Energy, EDO ANGI, and EDO (Canada) Ltd., EDO provides the industry with a "complete approach" to vehicle conversions, fueling stations, customer service and technical innovation.<P>
<LI>
EDO Energy is a group of experienced program managers that work with customers on special projects with a requirement for broad technical services, fund coordination and marketing management.<P>
<LI>
EDO ANGI is a full service packager and manufacturer of compressed natural gas refueling stations and vehicle conversion equipment.  The Company has installed more than 250 CNG refueling stations across the country, and distributed approximately 14,000 conversion kits to a broad spectrum of vehicle markets including passenger cars, trucks, school buses, forklifts, and marine vessels.<P>
<LI>
EDO (Canada) Ltd. is the manufacturer of all composite, long range EDO LiteRider Compressed Natural Gas (CNG) Cylinder.  At 1/3 the weight of traditional steel tanks and 1/2 the weight of aluminum tanks wrapped with fiberglass, the LiteRider cylinder is not only the lightest cylinder in the world, but also holds up to 30% more fuel than any other cylinder of any given size on the world market.  Manufactured at an ISO 9001 facility and certified to the industries highest standard for NGV cylinders (AGA/ANSI NGV-2; CGA B51 Part 2), the cylinder also meets the criteria established by the US Department of Transportation's FM VSS Standard #304.
</LI><P>
Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, EDO Corporation continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.
<P><P>

<H4>CONTACT:</H4>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Van Negris<BR>
Kehoe, White, Savage & Co., Inc. <BR>
(212) 888-1616 <P>
Eleanor Ryan<BR>
EDO (Canada) Ltd.<BR>
(403) 569-5456

</BLOCKQUOTE>
