<TITLE>Press Release: EDO Corporation Awarded $1.5 Million Contract by ADI Limited of Australia </TITLE>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Kehoe, White, Savage & Company, Inc.">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P><CENTER><I><B>Press Release</B></I></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Awarded<BR>$1.5 Million Contract by<BR>ADI Limited of Australia 
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  MAY 29, 1996  EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today announced that it has been awarded a $1.5 million subcontract from ADI Limited, Perth Facility, Bentley WA, Australia to supply its Tactical Data Link (TDL) systems to the Royal Australian Air Force.<P>

EDO's Tactical Data Link (TDL) systems will be used to support maritime operations and real-time data communications for P-3C Orion Maritime Patrol Aircraft.  The TDL systems will be supplied by EDO Combat Systems, a business unit of EDO Corporation, which is a leading supplier of low-cost, robust, tactical data link systems for use in shipboard, aircraft, mobile shore-based, and command center environments.<P>

Mr. Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation, stated:  "This Australian contract award demonstrates EDO's strong commitment to continued growth of our international command and control business.  We will continue to aggressively pursue additional business opportunities and apply the full breadth of our advanced technology to building business in this developing market."<P>

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.<P><P>

