<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation Reports<BR>1996 First Quarter Results;<P>Fifth Consecutive Quarter<BR>of Improvement in Net Income 
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY  April 23, 1996  EDO Corporation (NYSE:EDO) today reported operating results for the 1996 first quarter.<P>
Sales for the 1996 first quarter increased 26% to $26,281,000 from the $20,918,000 reported in the similar period a year ago.  Operating earnings increased 53% to $970,000 from $633,000 reported for the 1995 first quarter.  The increases are reflective of improving operations and represent a 12% increase in sales and a 4% increase in operating earnings over the 1995 fourth quarter.  The Company reported net earnings available for common shares of $650,000, or $0.11 per share, for the 1996 first quarter, compared to $109,000, or $0.02 per share, reported a year ago.<P>
The Company's order backlog at the end of the 1996 first quarter was $95,760,000, 8% higher than the $88,995,000 reported in the comparable 1995 period. The backlog includes the recently announced awards of contracts from Hughes Space and Communications Company for the production of earth sensors and Barry Controls for the production of solid-state electro-strictive actuators for use in advanced vibration control isolation systems.<P>
The Company also reported that it has completed negotiations, and has received a commitment from its bank, to extend the maturity date of the $15 million line of credit agreement for both short term borrowings and letters of credit to June, 1997 and to extend the option to cancel or refinance its ESOT borrowing to April 1, 2000.<P>
Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer, stated:  "Our fifth consecutive quarter of improvement reflects the successful execution of our strategic plan to return to profitability and strong liquidity.  We have proven that we have a strong company capable of performing in today's complex business environment."<P>
Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, the Company continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.<P>
NOTE:  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation World Wide Web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.<P><P>
