<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/edologo.gif"> </CENTER>
<P ALIGN=Center>[ <A HREF="../prlsmenu.html">List of Press Releases</A> | <A HREF="../irmenu.html">Investor Relations Home Page</A> | <A HREF="../../index.html">EDO Corporation Home Page</A> ]<P><HR><P>

<H2><CENTER> EDO Corporation<BR>Awarded $1.1 Million Boeing Contract 
</CENTER></H2><P>

COLLEGE POINT, NY - April 22, 1996 - EDO Corporation, (NYSE:EDO) announced today that it has been awarded a $1.1 million contract from the Military Airplanes Division of Boeing's Defense and Space Group.  The Company will be supporting Boeing as it executes its prime contract to develop "Weapons Carriage Technology" (WCT) for the United States Air Force, Wright Laboratory, Armament Directorate at Eglin Air Force Base.

The WCT program will develop new suspension and release equipment for use on future tactical military aircraft.  These aircraft will require equipment that is easily adaptable for use with both existing and new design weapons and that can also be readily used in either an internal weapon's bay or an external pylon.  WCT will also dramatically reduce the levels of maintenance and logistics required in addition to offering reduced weight.

Frank A. Fariello, President and Chief Executive Officer of EDO Corporation stated:  "Thehe Boeing/EDO relationship will ensure that WCT will benefit from the unique perspective that each company brings to the effort.  This award will serve to enhance the opportunities available to EDO as aircraft development programs, such as Joint Attack Strike Technology (JAST), begin to mature."

Principally a designer and manufacturer of advanced electronic, mechanical, acoustic and composite products for military, space, marine and commercial aviation markets, EDO Corporation continues to pursue the application of its sophisticated and diverse technologies to new commercial and industrial markets.

NOTE TO EDITORS:  Press releases and other EDO information are available on the EDO Corporation web site:  http://www.edocorp.com.

